  function showButtons() {
    var buttons = document.getElementById('questiontable');

    buttons.style.visibility = '';
    feedback.style.visibility = 'hidden';

  // Start script after loading page
  SoSciTools.attachEvent(window, 'load',
                         function() {
                           // Get buttons
                           var buttons = document.getElementById('questiontable');
                           // Hide buttons
                           buttons.style.visibility= 'hidden';
                           // Start timer
                           window.setTimeout(showButtons, 1500); // In milliseconds
                         }
  );
  
  // -->
    </script>

Thank you for showing interest in this study. Please read the following before starting:

Please complete this survey in one go. In other words, please only participate in this survey, if you have around 10 minutes that you can dedicate to it.

Before you start, please:

  • maximize your browser window
  • silence your phone, e-mail, music, and anything else distracting

Issues have been reported when using Internet Explorer. Please use another browser (by copy/pasting the link) for this study if possible.

Your participation in this study is very important to us. Please realize, however, that your data is only useful if you work in a concentrated and diligent fashion. Please select "I disagree" in the following question.

]]> This question is an attention check. Please realize that your data is only useful if you work in a concentrated and diligent fashion. Please select "I disagree" for this question. ]]> ]]> consent Consent form

Throughout this study you will engage in repeated choices between two options and will be asked to make estimates regarding these two choices. The study will take approximately 10 minutes to complete. We ask you to complete the survey in a setting which is quiet and offers no distractions for the duration of the experiment. No negative side effects are to be expected. Participation in the study is completely voluntary and you can withdraw from the study at any time without justification.

We ask for information about your gender, age, and education level. We do not ask for identifying personal information and make sure that all data is anonymous. By participating in this study, you agree that research data gathered for the study may be published or made available provided no identifying information is used.

  • I confirm that I understand the nature, method, and purpose of this study and the manner in which my data will be used. I have had the opportunity to reflect on this information.
  • I give permission and understand that my data will be used by the research as explained on the previous page. I understand that this information will be handled in accordance with applicable guidelines on handling research data.
  • I understand that I can withdraw from this study at any time without giving reasons by closing this browser window.
]]> ]]> Initializing Imagine you are a police officer and your task is to check two groups of people for weapons they might carry with them.

In each trial, you will be presented with two imaginary population groups, group 1 and group 2. Both groups of people possess a certain number of weapons (knives) and tools (rulers).

You will be instructed to choose between the two imaginary groups by clicking on the icon of the particular group. The tool or weapon that the person from the selected group has on them will then appear on the screen. The distribution of tools and weapons within groups will remain equal across all trials. In total there will be 100 trials.
